# Only the *.example.yaml are tracked. Your own settings.yaml / actions.yaml /
# kb.yaml / users.yaml stay out of git, so `git pull` can never overwrite what
# you tuned for your product — and onbo can keep changing its examples without
# ever giving you a merge conflict.
#
# To take one over: cp settings.example.yaml settings.yaml — the copy wins as
# soon as it exists. Until then onbo reads the example, so a fresh clone runs.
*.yaml
!*.example.yaml
